cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image classification, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves modeling spatio-temporal distributions and photographer biases, which are common themes in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of contextual information and presence-only observation data also suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the experiments involve multiple datasets and performance evaluation, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
